description: They live at the edge of everything - the boundary where something becomes nothing. They're not sure which side they're on.
name: Black Horizon

description: Grey market dealers in body modifications. Cybernetic, biological, skeletal. They upgrade what nature provided.
name: Bone Merchants

description: They bring clean endings. Every corpse burned, every diseased crop incinerated, every haunted ruin reduced to safe ash.
name: Brotherhood of Ash

description: The crown of bones. They rule through blood right and inscribe their will in edicts.
name: Carrion Throne

description: Nomadic explorers who chart probability-space. Their maps show routes that only exist sometimes, destinations that move.
name: Cartographers

description: The eternal substrate. Sun and moon, the four elements. The abiotic foundation.
name: Celestial Archons

description: Revolutionary fire-worshippers who believe destruction clears the way for new growth. Part arsonists, part prophets.
name: Children of the Ember

description: Their songs dissolve identity. Those who join the chorus forget who they were. Eventually, the song is all that remains.
name: Chorus of Oblivion

description: Subterranean farmers cultivating root vegetables and fungi. Their tunnels connect in ways surface-dwellers don't understand.
name: Clan of the Hidden Root

description: They worship a star that fell into nothing. They believe it waits at the bottom of the void, dreaming of return.
name: Cult of the Drowned Star

description: Long-haul data transport. Their ships are flying libraries, their crews notoriously well-read.
name: Engram Freighters

description: Rural insurgents who sabotage infrastructure and fight against enclosure. Some are bandits. Some are idealists. Most are desperate.
name: Fencebreakers

description: Builders who work in living tissue. Their constructions grow, heal, and hunger. Some of their buildings have learned to want.
name: Flesh Architects

description: The mechanics' guild. Their stamp means it meets spec. Their refusal means you're gambling.
name: Gearwright Circle

description: Keepers of the surplus. They turn bread into wealth and seeds into futures.
name: Granary Guilds

description: The tenders of flame and dough. Where wheat becomes bread.
name: Hearth Keepers

description: Kitchen witches who brew remedies, read tea leaves, and keep small magics alive. Their power is in the everyday.
name: Hearth Witches

description: Research institution dedicated to genomics. They study DNA like others study sacred texts, seeking meaning in the double helix.
name: Helix Conservatory

description: The aristocratic court. They deal in marriages, alliances, favors, and elegant betrayals. The rose has thorns.
name: House of Thorns

description: Priests who minister to machines. They hear the confession of gears, absolve the sins of circuits, and pray for the salvation of all mechanisms.
name: Iron Confessors

description: Armed protectors of refugee convoys and vulnerable settlements. Their sheep are people. Their wolves are anyone who threatens them.
name: Iron Shepherds

description: Twelve citizens who decide where water goes. Their decisions shape harvests and settle disputes older than memory.
name: Irrigation Jury

description: They guard secrets by ensuring they are never spoken. Information that enters their silence never leaves.
name: Keepers of Silence

description: Union workers who maintain the grid. Their monthly meetings are legendarily boring. The power must flow.
name: Kilowatt Collective

description: Every oath is a knot. Every promise a binding. They maintain the web of obligations that holds society together.
name: Knot-Shriners

description: A secret language spoken in lamp-flashes and candle-patterns. They coordinate across vast distances using only light.
name: Lantern Cant

description: A court of jesters, fools, and tricksters who've realized the cosmic joke. Their laughter is contagious - dangerously so.
name: Laughing Court

description: The enforcement arm of documentary reality. They collect what the ledgers say is owed. The worst punishment is ledger-death.
name: Ledger Bailiffs

description: Biological salvage swarm. They strip everything useful from dying ecosystems and move on. Part pest, part cleanup crew, all hunger.
name: Locusts

description: They weave tapestries that tell futures. The patterns emerge unbidden. They don't control the loom - they interpret it.
name: Loom Priests

description: The invisible hands that push and pull. Greed and fear dance eternal.
name: Market Spirits

description: Pure auditors who define the units of existence. Whoever defines measurement defines reality.
name: Measure Scribes

description: Dealers in recorded experience. They buy recollections from the desperate, sell them to the curious, and archive everything.
name: Memory Merchants

description: Masters of the grinding stone. They turn flour into bread at industrial scale.
name: Millwright's Union

description: Architects who construct buildings that remain stable across probability fluctuations. Their geometries were inherited from civilizations that no longer exist.
name: Monolith Masons

description: They trade in messages carried through moss networks and fungal relays. Slower than radio, but untraceable.
name: Mossline Brokers

description: The hidden network beneath. Moon-touched, death-fed, eternal recyclers. Spooky symbiosis with death itself.
name: Mycelial Web

description: Gatekeepers who control major transit points. Their keys open doors that shouldn't exist.
name: Nexus Wardens

description: Labor organizers who impose structure on chaotic workforces. Their methods are strict, their results undeniable.
name: Obsidian Will

description: Draconic contract enforcers. They guarantee deals with blood oaths and collect debts with dragonfire. Their word is law.
name: Order of the Crimson Scale

description: The hunters. They cull the weak and shepherd death.
name: Pack Lords

description: The invisible cullers. They thrive on density and crash on scarcity.
name: Plague Vectors

description: The tiny workers without whom no seed sets. Their absence collapses agriculture.
name: Pollinator Guild

description: Biological border guards preventing contamination. Their work prevents plagues nobody knows about.
name: Quarantine Sealwrights

description: Dockside operators who control port operations. They know which ships carry what and which cargo is fiction.
name: Quay Rooks

description: They assist in the birth of new patterns from chaos. What emerges isn't always what was expected. Not everything should be born.
name: Reality Midwives

description: The telecom company. Mind-bogglingly complex infrastructure, frustratingly mundane service.
name: Relay Lattice

description: Dancers whose movements stabilize unstable regions of space. Where they perform, reality holds together. Where they don't...
name: Resonance Dancers

description: Technical school for spacecraft propulsion. Their bureaucracy is legendary. Their approved systems don't explode unexpectedly.
name: Rocketwright Institute

description: Guardians of eternal flames in temples across the void. They tend fires that have burned since before memory.
name: Sacred Flame Keepers

description: Canal smugglers moving contraband through waterways that official maps don't show. Salt is their cover cargo.
name: Salt-Runners

description: Estate guards who protect agricultural land. They fight for the fields, not for glory.
name: Scythe Provosts

description: Tailors who encode information in fabric patterns. A trained eye reads origin, status, and secrets in the weave.
name: Seamstress Syndicate

description: Keepers of the genetic archive. Every biological pattern that sustains civilization.
name: Seedvault Curators

description: Navigators who map routes through probability-space. Where others see chaos, they see currents.
name: Star-Charter Enclave

description: Heavy-duty celestial mechanics maintaining ancient stellar infrastructure. They don't research new tech - they keep the old tech running.
name: Starforge Reliquary

description: Masters of the checkpoint. They receive edicts and forge them into law.
name: Station Lords

description: The gentle grazers. They eat the green and feed the strong.
name: Swift Herd

description: Artisans who forge instruments with properties that edge toward the mystical. They understand resonance at a level that approaches the quantum.
name: Symphony Smiths

description: Criminal oligarchs dealing in precision surveillance and blackmail. Their mirrors show what people hide.
name: Syndicate of Glass

description: Ecological engineers who design self-sustaining habitats. Sewage, air, nutrients - the unglamorous essentials.
name: Terrarium Collective

description: Mining consortiums and gem traders. Old money, patient money, money that thinks in generations.
name: The Gilded Legacy

description: The office that creates permanent records. Birth, death, property, citizenship. What they record becomes true.
name: The Indelible Precept

description: Broadcasters who transmit on frequencies that slip between official channels. Their programs reach listeners who didn't know they were tuned in.
name: The Liminal Osmosis

description: They walk the boundary between light and fabric, flame and thread. Their candles burn wicks spun from probability itself.
name: The Liminal Taper

description: They claim to observe from outside time itself. Their judgments are final because they've already seen all outcomes.
name: The Opalescent Hegemon

description: The rustling of the displaced. They appear from refuse and fade into death. Unmeasurable.
name: The Scavenged Psithurism

description: Pharmaceutical and medical supply arm of imperial authority. Their generosity comes with strings - dependency on their supply chains.
name: The Sovereign Ukase

description: Obsessive observers who stare into reality's structure until it stares back. Their mathematics touches things that shouldn't exist.
name: The Vitreous Scrutiny

description: Traveling repair crews in battered vans. They fix what others throw away.
name: Tinker Team

description: The shadow market. They fence stolen goods, launder currency, and broker information. Everything is for sale, including you.
name: Umbra Exchange

description: A covert sisterhood that moves through every level of society. They share information, protect their own, and arrange for problems to solve themselves.
name: Veiled Sisters

description: The green rhythm of growth and decay. Seeds become grass or trees, grain returns to earth.
name: Verdant Pulse

description: They administer the emptiness between stars. Their bureaucracy governs nothing, yet their edicts shape what might emerge.
name: Void Emperors

description: The chained ones. Bound by debt to the mystic dark. They sense the true void but cannot name it.
name: Void Serfs

description: Musicians who perform at the edge of known space. Their songs reach into the void, and sometimes the void sings back.
name: Void Troubadours

description: Masters of volcanic processes who harvest crystals from cooling magma. They read the earth's fire and know when to mine.
name: Volcanic Foundry

description: The great destroyer and renewer. Burns hot, leaves fertility behind.
name: Wildfire

description: The fermentation mystics. They read futures in rising dough and set initial conditions through sacred cultivation.
name: Yeast Prophets
